  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You can spend 2 @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-class-features.imsZ2GYUPlwCQqqy]{ki points} as an action to create a whip of water that shoves and pulls a creature to unbalance it. A creature that you can see that is within 30 feet of you must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes [[/r 3d10]] bludgeoning damage, plus an extra [[/r 1d10]] bludgeoning damage for each additional ki point you spend, and you can either knock it <strong>prone </strong>or pull it up to <strong>25 feet </strong>closer to you. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage, and you don't pull it or knock it prone.</p><section class=\"secret\" id=\"secret-vGhngvt6Q9MHNGgS\"><p><em>Note: After adding this feature to your character, set Resource Consumption to Item Uses: Ki: 2.</em></p><p><em>To roll additional damage, click the 1d10 button and deduct ki points manually.</em></p></section>",
